1. Paul Atkins' nomination as chairman of the US SEC has been approved by the Senate;
2. The White House: Tariff levels will be reduced to a general 10% during negotiations;
3. The US SEC approved options trading for spot Ethereum ETFs;
4. US stocks closed: Trump postponed trade policy, and the Nasdaq soared 12%;
5. Multiple addresses locked nearly half of CAKE's voting rights in advance, intending to lead the new governance proposal;
6. Goldman Sachs quickly lowered its expectations for a US recession;
7. Fed Musallem: A balanced monetary policy will be adopted as long as inflation expectations remain stable;
8. Fed minutes: All participants believed that it was appropriate to keep interest rates unchanged given the obvious uncertainty in the economic outlook;
9. Traders now expect the Fed to cut interest rates only three times this year, starting in June;
10. Fed minutes: Inflation may rise this year due to tariffs;
11. Wunder.Social completed a $50 million financing, led by Rollman Management;
12. Magic Eden announced the acquisition of a decentralized trading platform Slingshot.
